      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que\n$\\sum_{k=0}^\\infty \\Arctan\\Bigl(\\frac1{k^2+k+1}\\Bigr) = \\frac \\pi2$.\n(On pourra calculer $\\tan s_n$)",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\sum_{k=0}^\\infty \\Arctan\\Bigl(\\frac1{k^2+k+1}\\Bigr) = \\frac \\pi2\\)</span>. (On pourra calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\tan s_n\\)</span>)</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "a39eb153-cc00-456d-b660-c748c6f08e23",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$\\tan s_n = n+1$ par récurrence et\n         $s_n \\le \\sum_{k=0}^\\infty \\frac 1{k^2+k+1} \\le 1\n         + \\sum_{k=0}^\\infty \\frac1{n(n+1)} = 2$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\tan s_n = n+1\\)</span> par récurrence et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(s_n \\le \\sum_{k=0}^\\infty \\frac 1{k^2+k+1} \\le 1\n         + \\sum_{k=0}^\\infty \\frac1{n(n+1)} = 2\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
